PROBLEM:
#1 - Array Sum

Implement the method arraySum that takes as input a non-empty list of Integers numbers, 
and returns the sum of all numbers in the list.

Example: arraySum(new List {5, 2, 3}) evaluates to 10.

Hint 1:
Use the .size() function to obtain the size of the input list

Hint 2:
Use the [] notation or the .get(index) method to obtain the element at index.

Hint 3:
Declare an Integer to hold the sum and initialize it with 0. Use a for loop to add each 
elemenent in the list to the variable. Finally, return the calculated

-------------------------------
SOLUTION:

public static Integer arraySum(List<Integer> numbers) {
    // Declare an integer to hold the sum
    Integer sum = 0;
    // Loop through each number and add it to the sum
    for (Integer i = 0; i < numbers.size(); i++) {
        sum += numbers.get(i);
    }
    return sum;
}